app.p:
discussions of their own experiences or background with principals:


open-ended, general questions about principal’s school, faculty, students, and other working conditions;



inquiries about what the principal wants to accomplish through the coaching sessions;



initial, general discussions about the feedback that principals have been receiving. (note: Discussions in which coaches and principals review specific results from the feedback fall under ‘assessment and feedback’.)



conversations about the coaches’ and principals’ theories of leadership or management;



efforts to empathize with the principal about different conditions the principal faces;



reflective listening, in which he or she summarizes back what the principal has shared in order to verify what the coach is hearing.
